node.text:
To create the neon sign for our Japan Tasting Room, @b.k5.tokyo, we teamed up with Hidenobu Takahashi of @smileneon_official, one of Japan’s last remaining traditional neon benders with over twenty years of experience. The design, illustrated by our friend @msynkyma, updates our iconic logo with a blend of Japanese old-school Katakana script and Kanji reading “Brooklyn Brewery Tokyo.”
🎥 @joesoriero 
🎛 @ill__sugi @yugoease

#repost @thestonewallinn Today marks 52 years since the riot that became #Pride began. What happens next for the LGBTQ+ community is up to all of us! 

Swipe through to learn about our history and our future with @stonewallgives.

Photo by Brooklyn Brewery on June 28, 2021. May be an image of 7 people and text that says 'In the early hours of June 28, 1969, yet another raid on Stonewall Inn began. But this time, we fought back. Trans women and others in the community resisted arrest. And a riot began. INN'.

Photo by Brooklyn Brewery on June 28, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'By July 1st, The Stonewall Inn had become the gathering point for LGBTQ activists and was building the community that would fuel the growing gay rights movement.'.

Photo by Brooklyn Brewery on June 28, 2021. May be an image of 2 people and text that says 'On the first anniversary of the police raid on Stonewall, activists in NYC organized the Christopher Street Liberation March to cap off the city's first Gay Pride Week. Pride had begun.'.

Photo by Brooklyn Brewery on June 28, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'While we are proud of how far we've come, there is still so much work to do. That's why we have the Stonewall Inn Gives Back Initiative, the official charity of The Stonewall Inn. The work towards liberation isn't over yet. And we won't rest until LGBTO people everywhere are free. LOYELARESISTANCE STONEWALLSTANC'.
